StoryAsset.name: Short Post Match Cup Leg 1 of 2 Semifinal

keyValuePair.Value: How big a blow is that to your hopes?
It's a blow: defeat in the home leg for your %1s team. Did the occasion get to your players? What are your chances now of reaching the Final?
There's still everything to play for.

We're so close to the Final. Maybe the pressure told on the lads. But we know we can play better than we did here. We can go into the away leg with nothing to lose. It'll be up to us to get the first goal.
We've got goals in our team.

It was a pity we never imposed ourselves on %1s as an attacking force. We didn't really threaten, did we? Never looked like getting a positive result? But look: there's not much between the teams. If we can create chances for ourselves in the second leg, we can still reach the Final.
We got overrun, didn't we?

We knew they were good across midfield and we'd prepared for that, but our lads just couldn't get to grips with them. They overran us at times. It won't be easy now but, if we can get men around the ball better in the second leg, we've still got a chance of reaching the Final.
Have you definitely missed out on the Final now?
As soon as the first goal went in, your boys looked in trouble. Did the pressure get to them? Do you have to admit now that your chances of reaching the Final are gone?
We looked nervous out there.

We didn't do ourselves justice at all. The lads looked nervous, as if they were waiting for the worst to happen. But while we've got players who work as hard as ours do, we've always got a chance. We'll be massive underdogs now but we have to believe in ourselves.
We let them control the game.

We allowed them to have control for most of the game. The lads struggled out there, to be honest, and we didn't ever get into it as an attacking force. To reach the Final, we have to go away now and try to make something remarkable happen.
You'd probably say we're out of it now.

I didn't recognise that as a %1s performance. Very poor indeed. We'll struggle to reach the Final now. But there are 90 minutes left in the tie. Let's go there, be positive and get the first goal. Then who knows what might happen?
You have a lot to do at home now, don't you?
With the Final in sight, you've suffered a terrible first leg defeat. Your %1s team is famous for its fantastic fighting spirit, but surely even your boys won't believe they can come back from that?
We'll do what we can. It's a semi-final.

That was a big blow to our hopes of getting to the Final, that's for sure. We lost our shape and they were able to hurt us on the transitions. But we can't just feel sorry for ourselves. We have to give our fans something to cheer about in the second leg. Let's see what happens.
We'll have to make chances in the second leg.

For whatever reason, our lads just weren't at the races. We got swarmed over too often, gave up too much possession, and never got going as an attacking force in the game. Look, in front of our own fans, maybe we can create a few chances. If we can score early? Let's see what happens.
We need a miracle now.

We didn't play like a %1s team, did we? I'm sure nobody will give us a chance of getting to the Final now. Well, perhaps that'll take the pressure off and we'll be able to play like we know we can in the second leg, in front of our own fans.
How will you turn this semi-final around?
A narrow defeat for %1s in the first leg of the semi. How are you feeling? What will you have to do if you're to turn this tie round and qualify for the Final?
We still have a big chance.

It was a tight game and we're happy to have kept it to a narrow margin. If we take what we've learnt about the opposition now and prepare well, I think we can still turn the tie round in front of our own supporters.
We have to create chances.

The boys worked very hard here, gave everything for the team, but %1s put us under quite a bit of pressure. We weren't able to get forward often enough to create many goal-scoring opportunities. If we get chances in the second leg, though, we're capable of turning this tie round.
We need a plan.

We really struggled when it came to the fight for possession. That's where this game was lost. We'll need to look at the shape of the team and maybe the personnel for the return. We have to come up with a plan. I still believe we can reach the Final.
Does a draw here put you in a good position?
We know how strong your %1s team are at home. So is a draw in this first leg a pretty good result? Are you confident you can make it to the Final with the crowd roaring you on?
We have to be even more determined.

If we'd had a bit more composure when we were under pressure, it could have been even better tonight. The lads stuck together and made us competitive, though, and hopefully we can go one better in the second leg. Let's be even more determined. We want our supporters to be celebrating us reaching the Final.
We have to be pleased with a draw.
We have to be pleased with a draw.

We lost a bit of control in dangerous moments and the team had to suffer because of that. But a draw is a good result. We know we'll have our crowd right behind us in the second leg. If we can be more creative and find our touch in front of goal, I'm sure we can reach the Final.

We lost a bit of control in dangerous moments and the team had to suffer because of that. But a draw is a good result. We know we'll have our crowd right behind us in the second leg. If we can be more creative and find our touch in front of goal, I'm sure we can reach the Final.
I'm pretty confident.

We played well today and were a little unlucky not to win the game, in my opinion. Now it's up to us. It'll be a great atmosphere in front of our own fans. We'll do everything we can to reach the Final now.
Will you pay for not winning today?
Your team looked a little nervous in this first leg and you weren't able to earn an advantage to take to the return fixture. Does this draw make it hard now for your boys to reach the Final?
Of course it would have been better to win.

I'm sure we're not out of it yet. We were a bit sloppy defensively and that meant we had to spend more time and energy than I'd have wanted on winning the ball back. We didn't create enough. But we know what we have to do now to reach the Final. Don't write us off yet.
We might have more room to play.
We might have more room to play.

We were up against a very strong defensive team and we struggled to break them down. But, in front of their own fans, they'll push forward more and maybe that will leave room in behind for us strikers to exploit. Let's be sharp and then we can still do it!

We were up against a very strong defensive team and we struggled to break them down. But, in front of their own fans, they'll push forward more and maybe that will leave room in behind for us strikers to exploit. Let's be sharp and then we can still do it!
We can still go through, I believe.

Of course the plan was to establish a lead today but we weren't able to do that. But it's everything to play for in the second leg. It's winner-takes-all, right? I'm confident my lads will keep their heads and do what we need to do to reach the Final.
How is the tie balanced now?
We always expect %1s to score goals and create chances. But here you were strong defensively. Is a draw and a clean sheet a good result for your boys?
We've got ourselves into a good position.

The boys put in a lot of really good defensive work to earn us the draw. I'm very pleased with their effort and determination. It gives us the chance now to be more positive in the second leg, in front of our own fans, and get the goal we need to go through to the Final.
We've got an excellent team spirit.

Of course we wanted to win here. The boys gave everything for the team tonight, defending well and supporting each other the whole game. I'm just disappointed they couldn't take one of the chances we created. It'll be up to them to put that right in the second leg!
We want the fans to have something to celebrate.

We have to be happy with the draw and a clean sheet away from home. Now, let's have a great atmosphere at home. Of course we'll be more positive and I hope we'll score the goals we need to get us into the Final.
Was that a frustrating 90 minutes?
%1s are usually so confident and positive in home games. But tonight was different, against a very good opponent. A nil-nil draw means the pressure is on now in the away leg. Can your boys cope?
We can still reach the Final.

We're disappointed we didn't win. But the positive is we did a great job to keep a clean sheet. That means the tie's still wide open. We'll go into the away leg with something to fight for. We just need one goal. I still believe we're good enough to make it to the Final.
We should have taken our chances.

Look, our attacking play was never really convincing. Maybe the boys were feeling the pressure. We were committed to our work and did make one or two chances, but we didn't take them. At least we know exactly what we have to do now to get to the Final.
We always expect to score at home.

I thought we were the better team and I'm surprised we weren't able to put our chances away here. But it's only half-time and we've learnt a lot about our opponents in this game. Now we have to score a goal or two away from home to get us into the Final.
Was that the perfect game?
That has to be one of the best performances in %1s history. Such a comprehensive win away from home surely means you're already through to the Final. What are your thoughts?
Let's go again.

We never gave them the chance to get into the game and the lads pretty much controlled the entire 90 minutes. I want the same again from them in the second leg now. Our fans deserve to see us reach the Final in style.
We were ruthless.

Of course it was a fantastic display. We were ruthless in attack and that's given us a huge advantage. We will need to make sure we defend well at home now and don't let the opposition back into the tie.
We have to see this out now.

We know we have a big chance of reaching the Final now. We have to be professional in our preparations and approach the game positively in front of our own fans. I hope we'll all be celebrating together!
Are you favourites to reach the Final now?
This looked like a really tough game against a strong team. But your boys have come away with a hard-earned victory. You must be delighted. Have you got one foot in the Final now?
We mustn't let the opposition back into it.

I couldn't have asked for much more from the boys. That was a very good performance. But it's only half-time in the tie. We need to be positive and focused in the return leg if we're going to make it to the Final.
We won the big battles.

I think you saw the best of us in this first leg. We gave the opposition no time on the ball and used it well when we won possession. I'm very satisfied. Another display like that from the boys in the home leg and I think we will make it to the Final.
We'll need to be sharp.

We were very strong defensively and then we took advantage at the other end of the pitch. The challenge now for the boys is not to switch off. We need to make sure we don't let the opposition back into the tie in the return leg.

We were very strong defensively and then we took advantage at the other end of the pitch. The challenge now for the boys is not to switch off. We need to make sure we don't let the opposition back into the tie in the return leg.
Are you on the brink of the Final now?
That was a mature and professional %1s performance. Grabbing a two-goal advantage is a big bonus, too. Would you say your boys have almost booked their place in the Final now?
We have to repeat that performance.

We've put ourselves in a strong position, of course. But we will need to be at our best in front of our own fans now. It's not over yet. We have to make sure we don't concede the first goal if we want to reach the Final.
We were pretty impressive.

We never looked like we were going to give anything away. I was very impressed with our discipline and organisation. We'll be favourites to reach the Final now but, in the second leg, the lads will have to stay focused to make sure we don't let the opposition back into the tie.
Let's control the second leg, too.

We've definitely put ourselves in control of this semi-final. I hope we can give our fans something to celebrate in the second leg. The key will be for the lads to go out and look to dominate the game again, just like they did here.

We've definitely put ourselves in control of this semi-final. I hope we can give our fans something to celebrate in the second leg. The key will be for the lads to go out and look to dominate the game again, just like they did here.
Do you have the advantage now?
That was a very professional %1s performance. The two-goal advantage gives you some breathing space going into the second leg now. Would you say you were confident of reaching the Final?
We've still got work to do.
I'm very happy with how we played and the two-goal lead is a big positive. But one goal could change everything in the away leg. We aren't in the Final yet!
I hope we play that well again.

We were very good defensively and kept control of their attacking players. And we showed our quality going forward. I'm confident the lads can do the same again in the away leg. If they do, then we'll be able to celebrate reaching the Final.
We could have finished it off!

I think we still have work to do in the second leg. If we'd been a little more clinical and built on our lead, we'd already be in the Final. But I trust the boys to take any chances we create away from home. One goal would be enough to settle everything for us now.

I think we still have work to do in the second leg. If we'd been a little more clinical and built on our lead, we'd already be in the Final. But I trust the boys to take any chances we create away from home. One goal would be enough to settle everything for us now.
You must be pleased with the win?
That was a terrific game between two good teams. You must be happy to be taking an advantage into the second leg. What was the secret to your victory here?
It's all about attitude.

At this level, so much of the battle is psychological. We were mentally strong, confident and determined. It's a narrow margin, so we'll have to be at our best again in the second leg to be sure of reaching the Final.
The players won their individual battles.

Of course we're up against strong opponents, so the tie isn't over yet. But the lads have given themselves a great platform. If they can take the same attitude into the second leg, then I'm confident we can build on our advantage and make it through to the Final.
It'll be a tough second leg.
We know it's not over yet. They're a good team and they'll come at us in the second leg. It'll be up to the lads to soak up any pressure, stay calm, and see us through to the Final.
A classic %1s performance. Are you into the Final now?
Your fans will be proud of that %1s performance. It was a crushing win for your boys. Do you think that'll be enough to take you through to the Final now?
We'll be positive again.

I'm very pleased with the performance and it was a great result. But %1s go into every game to win and the next leg will be no different. We'll be positive and I hope that will be enough to take us into the Final.
We're almost there.

I thought some of our attacking play was world-class: we looked pacy, intelligent and ruthless in front of goal. We'll just have to make sure we're strong defensively in the second leg now and don't give the opposition any chance to get back into the tie.
We're favourites now, that's for sure.

It was a great win and I'm confident we can make it through to the Final, of course. We have to be calm and professional now in the return leg. We can't afford to let opponents this good any kind of opportunity to get back into the tie.
